cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the concept of inhibition in memory and its application in Computer Science for optimizing information retrieval in Personal Information Management. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Cybernetics (cs.CY), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Among these, cs.HC and cs.IR are the most likely categories as they directly relate to the paper's focus on the efficiency of information processing and retrieval. Cs.CL is also relevant as it discusses the use of inhibitory mechanisms in natural language processing. Cs.CY and cs.NE are less likely but still possible as they deal with the application of inhibitory principles in cybernetic systems and neural networks, respectively.
